trade_description:
Egnatia Odos A.E. is a Greek company which was created in September 1995 as a product of discussions between the European Community and the Greek Government to advance the implementation of the second Community Support Framework. It is principally engaged in the management of design and construction, including the maintenance, and exploitation of the Egnatia Motorway, which extends from Igoumenitsa to Kipoi (Alexanroupolis). Egnatia Odos is managed by a nine- member board of directors with a registered head office in Thermi, Greece. Aside from its main axis, the company also designs and constructs sections of the nine Vertical Axes, which connect the Balkans and the wider Southeastern Europe with the Egnatia Motorway, the ports at the Aegean Sea and the airports of North Greece.
Egnatia Odos has entered a contract with an international consultancy firm, Kellog Brown & Root, as project manager. Other partners include J/V Sogelerg- OMEK-Lahmeyer, J/V De Leuw Cather Overseas, J/V Dorsch-Scetautoute-ADO, J/V Thales-OMEK, J/V Parsons-SÁLFO and J/V ADO-Scetauroutes. The company is a full member of The World Road Association, a non-profit organization that deals with road infrastructure construction and management issues.
The company's sole sharerholder is the State, but it operates by private sector economic and financial criteria, under the superintendence of the Ministry of Environment, Physical Planning and Public Works. Its aim is the management of design and construction, the maintenance, and exploitation of the Egnatia Motorway, its Vertical Axes as well as of other projects within or outside the Greek territory.

IEGSP, otherwise known as IGRETEC (Intercommunale pour la Gestion et la Réalisation d'Etudes techniques et Economiques), is a Belgian company engaged in the provision of consultancy services with expertise in the field of economic development. The company was incorporated in 1946, listed as co-operative society with limited liability.
In 1983, IEGSP has merged with ADEC (an inter-commune of economic development), subsequently forming the organization IGRETEC. Based in Belgium, the company has corporate head office located in Cherleroi. It is also active in the provinces of Hainaut, Brabant Wallon, Namur as well as Liège.
The company's staff of engineers, architects and technicians provides technical expertise in the development of public buildings, territorial development, town planning, real estate management and other related activities. The company also offers competency in various fields including water, energy, real estate as well as economy and tourism sectors. In partnership with local communities, the company has initiated a number of modernization projects in the areas of Charleroi and the South-Hainaut. One of its projects is the management and development of Charleroi Ai"

sector_code: M72100 - Forschung und Entwicklung im Bereich Natur-, Ingenieur-, Agrarwissenschaften und Medizin
trade_description:
Nordex Energy GmbH is an enterprise active in the wind energy sector. The company is primarily involved in provision of wind energy generating systems and solutions.
The company is a manufacturer of high-capacity wind turbine generators (WTG), specializing in the production of horizontal axis large turbines (1 MW) as well as horizontal axis medium turbines (from 100 kW to 1 MW). The overall technical design includes the development of rotor blades with a length of up to 45 meters and integrated electrical and control technology for wind turbines.
Its production plant in Rostock, Germany is engaged in the manufacture of turbine nacelle, the rotor blades and the electrical switching cabinets and execute a first test run of the WTG. The company's plant is certified according to DIN ISO 9001 (quality management).
The company also provides wind energy services to its clients, ranging from consultancy to contract R&D, design, project management, monitoring, repair as well as testing training, turbine design and wind farm development.
The company's ultimate parent is Nordex AG, which is a management holding company with headquarters in Norderstedt. The company's operations in Germany began in 1992 and has been incorporated as private limited firm in September 1999. The company also has a number of subsidiaries active in China and Greece.

trade_description:
Skotan S.A is a Poland-based company which is principally involved in the tannery industry. The company is engaged in the manufacture of calf leather and calf sides for the production of footwear, pig leather, pig splits used for lining, and plastic film covered leather. The company was established in 1859 by Dawid Spitzer in Skoczów. The company has a registered business address mainly located in Skoczow, Poland.
The company's main products are calf leather (which originates from Poland) for footwear, haberdashery and clothing; calf sides for footwear and haberdashery; pig leather for lining and haberdashery; pig splits for linings; and plastic-film-covered leather for footwear, haberdashery and clothing. Skotan has its own chemical sewage treatment plant. The export of the goods constitutes nearly a half of the production. Skotan also owns two warehouses, which serves the companies producing tanning agents.
The company is a publicly traded corporation listed in the Warsaw Stock Exchange and is one of the top 500 companies in Europe. The company is also a part of Alchemia S.A., a public company listed in the Warsaw Stock Exchange which is principally engaged in the manufacture of leather.
With its aim to meet its customer's needs, the company extends its interest to the oil industry. The company agrees to acquire 100% of Eurochem Sp. z o.o. from an individual investor. Eurochem holds a concession for trading in liquid fuels and diesel.
Furthermore, Skotan is engaged in a campaign to reduce the harmful impact of leather production on the environment by capital expenditure, formal and legal actions, and organizational solutions. The company is a holder of a Cleaner-Production Company Certificate.
